do we do this empty check for manufacturer elsewhere? 
For SparePartNumber, I know we do it because most companies don't support SparePartNumber

We didn't have that check. We are getting empty Manufacturer without that check,
 Patch #6 has the output

"@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Systems/system/PCIeDevices/pcie_card10",
  "@odata.type": "#PCIeDevice.v1_9_0.PCIeDevice",
  "Id": "pcie_card10",
  "Manufacturer": "",
  "Model": "6B87",
  "Name": "PCIe Device",

But isn't that on us to fill out the backend?
I don't see a check for empty on other resources with Manufacturer 
E.g.
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/blob/5e7e2dc585dc7a7e62d2b648b541e7f50c39ea5d/redfish-core/lib/storage.hpp#L230

We discussed in discord years ago (the gerrit commit was https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/38044) and the direction was no empty checks except like SparePartNumber. 
We can revisit this but let's be consistent
Done
